// ref-005-multiple-refs.scrml
// Several references in one file. Tests: multiple user state types instantiated
// side-by-side. State type names must not collide with built-in HTML element
// names (E-STATE-005), so we use `siteHeader` / `siteFooter`.

< siteHeader title(string)>
    <h1>${title}</>
</>

< siteFooter year(number)>
    <p>Copyright ${year}</>
</>

<div class="page">
    <siteHeader title="My Page"></>
    <main>
        <p>Content</>
    </>
    <siteFooter year="2026"></>
</>
